            <div class="right">
            <h1>Devgiri</h1>
            <p>Devagiri Fort, also known as Daulatabad or Deogiri, is a historic fortified citadel located in Devagiri village near Aurangabad, Maharashtra, India. It was the capital of the Yadava dynasty (9th century–14th century CE), for a brief time the capital of the Delhi Sultanate (1327–1334), and later a secondary capital of the Ahmadnagar Sultanate (1499–1636)</p>
            <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daulatabad_Fort"><input type="button" value="Read More" class="btn"></a>
